 the university augments the graduate experience and fosters a close alignment between faculty and graduate students.“UNT has faculty who are very excited about what they do and who are really invested in their students. I love that I’m able to interact with my advisor and other faculty members on a regular basis.”Natalie PardePh.D. student in Computer Science and EngineeringNSF Graduate Research Fellowship recipientOutstanding faculty and research facilitiesMany of our faculty members have been recognized for their teaching and scholarship by various scientific, educational and professional organizations. You can learn from National Academy of Engineering members, National Academy of Sciences members, Grammy Award winners and nominees, and Fulbright award winners, among others.You also can conduct individual research or collaborate on research projects in any of our 44 research institutes and centers. Research opportunities extend beyond the campus with field stations as far away as the sub-Antarctic region of Chile and the sub-Arctic region of Alaska.An extraordinary library systemUniversity Libraries are the heart of learning and research at UNT. With cataloged holdings of 7 million print and digital items and the UNT Digital Library ranking among the top 30 world repositories and among the top 10 national repositories, the library offers millions of pages of historical and unique content to researchers and scholars around the world.Dissertation and statistical supportThe Toulouse Graduate School offers a Dissertation Boot Camp and other specialized workshops, many of which are available online for your convenience. The Graduate Student Writing Support office can help you with writing and the Office of Research Consulting offers assistance with statistical analyses.Location, location, locationOur strategic location is the perfect place to be while earning your doctorate. The Dallas-Fort Worth area has one of the highest concentrations of Fortune 500 companies in the U.S. and is rich in job, cultural and learning opportunities. Denton, named “the best college town in Texas,” combines a family-friendly hometown feel with a vibrant music and arts scene. Enrolled students ride free on the bus system in Denton, making it easier to enjoy the many events and activities around town.ApplyNowRequestInformationTalk toan Advisor Visit Us Eagle Student Services Center 1147 Union Circle, ESSC #354 (UPS/FedEx) Denton, Texas 76203-5459 Mail Us 1155 Union Circle #305459 Denton, Texas 76203-5017 Contact Us 940-565-2383 Site last updated on May 09, 2017 Disclaimer| AA/EOE/ADA| Privacy| Electronic Accessibility| State of Texas Online| Emergency Preparedness| THECB Online Resume System Student Consumer Information| UNT Compliance Hotline| Governors Committee on People with Disabilities| Texas Veterans Portal| UNT Home Site last updated on May 09, 2017 | Important Links 